body.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT, Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the Counties of King and Kitsap.
The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County Greeting:

We command you, that you have the body of William W. Tinkham by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said Wiliam W. Tinkham shall be called or charged, before the HON. Roger S. Greene R.A. Jones, Judge of the aforesaid Court at the hour of 2 o'clock P.M. on the 14th day of Sept 1887, at the Court Room in Seattle W.T. to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said William W. Tinkham And have you then and there this writ.
WITNESS THE HON. R.A. Jones, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 14th day of Sept A.D. 1887
Filed Sept. 14th, 1887 W.E. Ledgerwood, Clerk By H. T. Hannon, Deputy
Service of the within writ acknowledged the 14th day of Sept 1887 at Port of Seattle King County W.T.
